WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:02.360
All right, my name is Joseph Sepp Spritzma.

00:02.360 --> 00:04.920
I'm with the Center for the Future of Arizona.

00:04.920 --> 00:06.400
I'm the regional project manager

00:06.400 --> 00:09.680
for College Career Pathways in Southeast Arizona,

00:09.680 --> 00:13.360
Cochise, Scram, Greenlee, Santa Cruz counties.

00:13.360 --> 00:15.440
I'm here today at Biosphere 2

00:15.440 --> 00:18.200
with the high school students from all over Arizona,

00:18.200 --> 00:21.320
specifically a group that I'm connected to in Wilcox

00:21.320 --> 00:25.360
for the space design competition, regional competition.

00:25.360 --> 00:28.000
And I just wanted to follow up and say

00:28.080 --> 00:31.920
that the experience was incredible,

00:31.920 --> 00:34.360
transformational and inspiring.

00:34.360 --> 00:37.600
These students in a 24-hour period

00:37.600 --> 00:41.040
took an RFP for a space colony

00:41.040 --> 00:45.000
and developed it together into a professional

00:45.000 --> 00:47.440
and well-organized

00:50.320 --> 00:55.000
presentation that would be acceptable for industry.

00:55.000 --> 00:57.000
They worked with mentors from Boeing,

00:57.000 --> 00:59.480
from the International Space Station,

00:59.480 --> 01:02.080
from University of Arizona,

01:02.080 --> 01:06.000
from all over the state to work to accomplish this.

01:06.000 --> 01:09.520
And if you have not been involved in one of these

01:09.520 --> 01:10.720
or unaware of it,

01:10.720 --> 01:13.040
I would highly suggest that you go take a look at it

01:13.040 --> 01:16.040
on the website and that you take an opportunity

01:16.040 --> 01:19.400
to even volunteer and get involved with this competition.

01:19.400 --> 01:21.800
It is mesmerizing.

01:21.800 --> 01:24.200
And I'm just so glad to have been here

01:24.200 --> 01:25.840
to support these students from Wilcox

01:25.840 --> 01:27.640
and from around Arizona

01:27.640 --> 01:31.200
and to support things like STEM, STEM education,

01:31.200 --> 01:35.240
career pathways, and college and career exploration

01:35.240 --> 01:36.800
in aerospace and beyond.

01:36.800 --> 01:38.720
It was magnificent.

01:38.720 --> 01:39.560
Thank you.

